      summary: "A shift from voluntary registration toward a national statutory framework, still consolidating.",
      body: "India's National Commission for Allied and Healthcare Professions (NCAHP), established by the NCAHP Act 2021, launched its official website on 29 October 2024 and began functioning operationally in 2024, spearheading creation of state-level allied-health councils. Occupational therapy is one of ~10 covered disciplines, with the Act recognizing OTs' authority to practice independently — a shift away from the prior voluntary/patchwork registration system.",
